    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix DRX configuration not properly activating after successful setup\n\n### Summary\nThe `eNB_Config_Local_DRX()` function in the MAC layer was not properly setting the `cdrx_configured` flag to `true` after successfully configuring DRX parameters. This caused the system to behave as if DRX was not configured even when the configuration completed successfully.\n\nAdditionally, error handling in the function was incomplete - when invalid DRX parameter values were provided, the function would log errors but continue execution, potentially leading to incorrect DRX configuration.\n\nThis fix ensures that:\n1. When DRX configuration is successful, `cdrx_configured` is set to `true` \n2. When DRX configuration fails due to invalid parameters, the function returns early\n3. Error cases properly reset the `cdrx_configured` flag to `false`\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/config.c`: Fixed `eNB_Config_Local_DRX()` function to properly set `cdrx_configured = true` after successful configuration and improved error handling\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE with valid DRX parameters using RRC connection reconfiguration\n2. Observe that after the configuration is processed by `eNB_Config_Local_DRX()`, the `cdrx_configured` flag remains `false` \n3. This causes the scheduler to not apply DRX-specific logic even though DRX parameters were configured\n4. When invalid DRX parameters are sent, the function logs errors but continues execution, potentially leaving the UE in an inconsistent state\n\nThe fix ensures that after successful DRX configuration, `cdrx_configured` is properly set to `true`, allowing the scheduler to correctly apply DRX behavior.\n"
}